You are working in Karen ownership: architecture, backend core, shared
contracts, LLM, repository process, docs, CI, and Cursor rules.

Allowed by default:

- backend TypeScript structure;
- backend routes/services/ws;
- shared Zod contracts;
- LLM endpoints, prompts, adapters, validation;
- npm workspace configuration;
- repo scripts;
- CI and PR workflow;
- Cursor rules and team documentation.

Do not add production-only complexity unless explicitly requested:

- no auth;
- no complex database;
- no large deployment platform;
- no broad dependency upgrades unrelated to the task.

For foundation or architecture changes:

- preserve `docs/baseline-checklist.md`;
- update human docs when rules or architecture change;
- keep `.cursor/rules` short and directive;
- mention contract changes in PR descriptions;
- avoid changing Sergey/Vasily product zones unless the task requires it.

Before merge-level work:

- run `npm run typecheck`;
- run `npm run build`;
- start the project with `./start.sh`;
- perform relevant manual checks.
